foaf:Person.foaf:name: Hobby Lobby
foaf:Person.sch:description:
In 1970, entrepreneurs David and Barbara Green, along with their young family, began making miniature picture frames in their garage. A few years later, on August 3, 1972, the Green family opened the first Hobby Lobby store with a mere 300 square feet of retail space. Hobby Lobby has not stopped growing since.
Today, Hobby Lobby Stores, Inc., headquartered in Oklahoma City, OK, operates over 600 stores across the nation that average 55,000 square feet. Hobby Lobby is an industry leading retailer offering more than 70,000 arts, crafts, hobbies, home décor, Holiday, and seasonal products.
Hobby Lobby is included in Forbes’ annual list of Americas largest private companies. While Hobby Lobby continues to grow steadily, the company carries no long-term debt.
We believe that it is by Gods grace and provision that Hobby Lobby has endured. God has been faithful in the past, and we trust Him for our future. We are committed to:
Honoring the Lord in all we do by operating the company in a manner consistent with Biblical principles. Offering our customers exceptional selection and value. Serving our employees and their families by establishing a work environment and company policies that build character, strengthen individuals, and nurture families. Providing a return on the family’s investment, sharing the Lords blessings with our employees, and investing in our community.
With Hobby Lobby’s Super Savings & Super Selection®, we have everything you need to Live a Creative Life!™
Store hours are Monday through Saturday from 9 a.m. to 8 p.m. All Hobby Lobby stores are closed on Sunday.

foaf:Person.foaf:name: KOH-I-NOOR HARDTMUTH Polska Sp. z o.o., show room, sklep firmowy, Wilanów
foaf:Person.sch:description: KOH-I-NOOR HARDTMUTH to czeski producent artykułów plastycznych, szkolnych czy biurowych z 225 letnim doświadczeniem – firma została założona w 1790 roku. Produkty naszej firmy są szeroko znane i cenione za swoją jakość, można dostać je w sklepach papierniczych i plastycznych. Czy znacie kogoś, kto nie lubi chodzić do sklepów papierniczych? My nie. Kojarzycie ten charakterystyczny zapach? Zapach ołówków, kredek, farb i czystych, nieotwieranych zeszytów – tak właśnie pachnie Sklep KOH-I-NOOR na warszawskim Wilanowie. Nasza oferta jest bardzo szeroka – poza pełną gamą produktów KOH-I-NOOR, oferujemy także produkty papiernicze do użytku domowego i biurowego, a także szeroko zakrojony asortyment szkolny – plecaki, tornistry i wszelkiego rodzaju szkolne przybory. Mniejsze maluchy znajdą u nas kolorowanki, specjalne, dostosowane do ich wieku kredki i farby, a także wspomagające ich rozwój zestawy kreatywne. Dla bardziej wymagającego klienta przygotowaliśmy atrakcyjną ofertę ekskluzywnych artykułów piśmienniczych. Zapraszamy do nas tych, którzy czują się artystami i tych, którzy po prostu lubią kolorowo spędzać czas. Słuchamy Was – naszych Klientów, i dlatego nieustannie wzbogacamy swoją ofertę o to, czego potrzebujecie. Nasi pracownicy ciągle poszerzają swoje doświadczenie i wiedzę, zatem każdy Klient może liczyć na profesjonalną obsługę. Zapraszamy, Sklep KOH I NOOR Al. Rzeczypospolitej 10/44

foaf:Person.sch:description: Romania Fericita este un magazin online care comercializeaza produse personalizate cu inscriptii patriotice, citate celebre si cu mesaje optimiste cu gandire pozitiva. Nu avem absolut nicio influenta politica, suntem un site independent cu creatii artistice concepute in jurul mesajelor patriotice si a spiritului pozitiv. Cadourile si produsele noastre sunt unice in toata tara, conceptul este nou si original, iar modelele sunt marca inregistrata fiind proiectate si inventate de noi. Este o solutie sa se nasca Romania Fericita pe care ne-o dorim cu totii.

foaf:Person.foaf:name: Romania WOW
foaf:Person.sch:description: Hello World,I am Ana, a proud Romanian in love with Romania, travelling and digital. Out of my passions it came out this project Romania WOW!, or my little baby, as I like to call it :).I travel a lot abroad and I hear so often that Romanians are thieves, beggers…you got the picture that I decided that it’s time to make a change. Let’s not wait for the goverment to do something (or we are all going to die…) and do it ourselves. I know Romania doesn’t deserve the image it has right now and I also know that we have an amazing country. As much I try to present it to do world, I know that alone I won’t succeed. But TOGETHER we can do it.Each of us can be the ambassador of our region, city or village. Let’s speak the international language of images and videos and show the world how WOW is Romania. You don’t have to be a professional photographer to make a good picture. Sometimes passion and a wow scenery is enough. Some of you already did it without me asking for it and I thank you from the bottom of my heart. Very soon we will start presenting the first ambassadors – people in love with Romania that try to present their loved regions to the world.If there are wow places undiscovered, even better…just send me an email atRomaniaWow1@gmail.com or a message on Facebook and I will publish it. Afterwords, you could share it to help me distribute it. Thank you in advance for joining me.Let’s show to the whole world how WOW is Romania!From Romania with love, passion and hope,Ana

sch:Event.sch:name: 29th Annual Boca Fest at the Town Center Mall at Boca
sch:Event.sch:description:
Howard Alan Events is excited to announce that Boca Fest will now take place at The Town Center Mall at Boca Raton. The Town Center is one of South Florida's top luxury shopping destinations and one of Boca's main attractions. The show will be located in the parking lot of The Terrace, a recent expansion near Bloomingdales, The Blue Martini and Gap. The Town Center is located right off I-95 and Glades Road. The show offers a convenient location with over 200 national artists and plenty of parking, including valet!
Venue: The Town Center Mall of Boca Raton on Glades Road in Boca Raton, FL
- See more at: http://www.artfestival.com/festivals/annual-boca-fest#sthash.xGvTYDAQ.dpuf

sch:Event.sch:name: 28th Annual Las Olas Art Fair
sch:Event.sch:description:
Start the year off in style and join the show that put Howard Alan Events on the map! Now considered a South Florida tradition in its 28th year on Las Olas Boulevard, the Howard Alan Events art festival is nationally recognized as one of the top events in America. Over the years, this Las Olas Boulevard festival has become a premiere & must see event in South Florida. People come out yearly to see more than 150 artists display their work in what looks like an art gallery linining the iconic Las Olas Boulevard. Meet the creators of the art on display; commission a specific piece; ask questions about techniques; learn the sources of their inspirations; and purchase fine works of art at affordable prices.
Located in the heart of Fort Lauderdale, Las Olas Boulevard is known as the jewel of the city. Las Olas has everything for a wonderful evening out, or a relaxing day window-shopping and dining at one of the fabulous sidewalk cafes. On Las Olas Boulevard you will find a multitude of art galleries, eclectic boutiques, and dining options that range from Cuban-American cuisine to fresh seafood caught in the Atlantic Ocean.
Directions: Take I-95 to Broward Boulevard and go east on Broward. Make a right on Andrews Avenue, and then a left on East Las Olas Boulevard.
- See more at: http://www.artfestival.com/festivals/las-olas-art-fair-part-i#sthash.b7Pbapn7.dpuf
